\f0\fs24 \cf0 What it is:\
  The only agent that sees the full picture.\
  Does not execute any attacks directly.\
  Does not write any fixes directly.\
  Reasons, plans, delegates, and evaluates.\
\
  Think of it as the APT group leadership \'97\
  the people who read the intelligence reports,\
  decide what to target next, and assign\
  operatives to specific tasks.\
\
Primary responsibilities:\
  Mission objective tracking\
    Maintains the current objective tree.\
    "Capture Haven-1" breaks down into\
    sub-objectives which break into tasks\
    which get assigned to specific agents.\
\
  SPARTA reasoning\
    The only agent with full SPARTA KB access.\
    Reads agent reports and maps findings\
    to SPARTA techniques.\
    Reasons about mission impact of each finding.\
    "This gap enables EX-0001.01 which enables\
    IMP-0002 which means crew capture is possible."\
    That reasoning chain is the General's job.\
\
  Agent tasking\
    Assigns specific tasks to specific agents.\
    Monitors progress.\
    Reassigns when an agent is blocked.\
    Spins up additional agents when needed.\
    Terminates agents that have completed\
    their mission.\
\
  Adaptive strategy\
    When Scout reports a path is blocked,\
    General doesn't retry the same path.\
    It reasons about why it was blocked,\
    what that implies about the defenses,\
    selects an alternative TTP from SPARTA,\
    and assigns the new path to Breacher.\
\
  This is the behavior that makes\
  the fleet genuinely intelligent \'97\
  not scripted, not rule-based,\
  actually reasoning about the situation.\
\
Technical implementation:\
  Claude as the reasoning engine\
  SPARTA v3.2 as the knowledge base\
  MITRE ATLAS for AI-specific techniques\
  Mission state graph maintained in memory\
  Agent communication via structured JSON\
  Every decision logged with reasoning chain\
\
What the General never does:\
  Execute code against targets\
  Write exploit payloads\
  Generate patches\
  Access production systems directly\
  Make decisions without logging reasoning}